\title{Matrix which squares to -1}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-07-18}
\taxon{example}
\import{ela}

\p{Consider the matrix
##{\mat{J} = \begin{bmatrix}0 & -1\\ 1 & 0\end{bmatrix}.}
Then
##{\mat{J}^{2} = \begin{bmatrix}-1 & 0\\0 & -1\end{bmatrix} = -\mat{I}_{2}.}
Thus #{\mat{J}} is a matrix which "looks like" #{i=\sqrt{-1}} in the complex numbers.}